Here is the suggested fix for org.eclipse.hyades.test.tools.ui.common.internal.report.jscrib.ReportDataUtils:

In the findAllReferencedTestSuites method the block object should be checked if it's null.

    public static List findAllReferencedTestSuites(TPFTestSuite ts){
        List referencedTestSuites = new LinkedList();
        //- Step 1. Add the parameter test suite:
        referencedTestSuites.add(ts);
        //- Step 2. Add all the invoked test suites:
        IImplementor implementor = ts.getImplementor();
        if (implementor != null){
            IBlock block = implementor.getBlock();
            if (block != null)
            	addBlockReferencedTestSuites(referencedTestSuites, block);
        }
        return referencedTestSuites;
    }


I suspect this only happens when the testsuite does not have any associated test executions.
